{"lemma":"عِبْرَةٌ","slug":"عِبْرَةٌ","root":"ع.ب.ر","root_slug":"ع-ب-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ب-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عِبْرَة","root":"عبر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":6},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27833"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"example, lesson, warning","examples":[{"text":"لَقَدْ كَانَ فِي قَصَصِهِمْ عِبْرَةٌ لِأُولِي الْأَلْبَابِ","english":"There is a lesson in the stories of such people for those who understand."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a tear before it overflows, a sobbing, the first sign of weeping","examples":[{"text":"فَفَاضَت دُمُوعُ الْجَحْمَتَيْنِ بِعَبْرَةٍ … عَلَى الزُبِّ حَتَّى الزُبِّ فِي المَاءِ غَامِس","english":"And the tears of the two eyes overflowed without sobbing … over the beard, until the beard was dipping into water"},{"text":"أسندتْ رأسها إلى صدري وسالت عبراتها.","english":"She leant her head on my chest where slight tears flew."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ع ب ر (ʕ b r). Compare to عَبْر (ʕabr, “crossing”)."},"ipa":["/ʕib.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27833","headword_ar":"عِبْرَةٌ","root":"Ebr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAiEotibaAru","text_ar":"الاِعْتِبَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An admonition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exhortation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in iii. 11):"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an admonition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exhortation, by which one takes warning"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"example:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel in xxiii. 21:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing by the state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition, of which one is admonished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reminded, and guided,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"directed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in xxiii. 21:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEotibaArN","text_ar":"اِعْتِبَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a being admonished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reminded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; but meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cause of being admonished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a warning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an example"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Jel in xvi. 68:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEotibaArN bimaA maDaY","text_ar":"اِعْتِبَارٌ بِمَا مَضَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~EaAZN","text_ar":"اِتّعَاظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta*ak~urN","text_ar":"تَذَكُّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning, in like manner,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cause of being admonished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reminded, by what has passed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an indication,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evidence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd and Jel in xxiv. 44, and Bd in xvi. 68,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whereby one passes from ignorance to knowledge:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in xvi. 68:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a state"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of things"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumstances"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whereby, from the knowledge of what is seen, one arrives at the knowledge of what is not seen;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEotibaArN","text_ar":"اِعْتِبَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (B, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wonderful thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as serves as a warning"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an example"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EibarN","text_ar":"عِبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, TA.) ―         -b2-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"account,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"estimation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"regard, in which a thing is held in respect of predicamental order;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEotibaArN","text_ar":"اِعْتِبَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) [Hence the common phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA Eiborapa bihi","text_ar":"لَا عِبْرَةَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"No regard is due to it."},{"kind":"text","text":"]       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EibaArapN","text_ar":"عِبَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Msb","B","TA","A","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}